fields.header: Maxx Crosby (ankle) active for Week 3
fields.description: Maxx Crosby (ankle) is officially active for Week 3 for the Las Vegas Raiders against the Carolina Panthers. (Source: Las Vegas Raiders on Twitter )
fields.fantasy_impact: Crosby was able to pass through pregame warmups successfully, and will likely have plenty of opportunities to pressure quarterback Andy Dalton against a dismal Carolina offensive line Sunday.

fields.header: Christian McCaffrey (Achilles) to see specialist in Germany
fields.description: Christian McCaffrey is seeing a specialist in Germany regarding his Achilles tendinitis. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: The status of McCaffrey remains up in the air. There should be another update on his status following this visit. In the meantime, Jordan Mason should remain an RB1 for fantasy managers.

fields.header: Malik Nabers suffers concussion in Week 4 loss
fields.description: Malik Nabers left Thursday night's 20-15 loss to Dallas late after suffering a concussion. Before exiting, Nabers caught 12-of-15 targets for 115 yards. He also carried the ball once for minus-four yards. (Source: Tom Pelissero on X)
fields.fantasy_impact: This is obviously not ideal news for both Giants and fantasy managers alike. Nabers has been a revelation as a rookie, having already caught 35-of-52 targets for 386 yards and three touchdowns through his first four career NFL games. Nabers was officially diagnosed with a concussion and his status moving forward should be monitored during New York's 10-day break. The Giants' next game is October 5 against the Seahawks in Seattle.

fields.header: A.J. Brown (hamstring) ruled out for Week 4 against Buccaneers
fields.description: A.J. Brown (hamstring) has been ruled out for Week 4 by the Philadelphia Eagles against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Brown will miss a third consecutive contest due to the hamstring injury, joining DeVonta Smith (concussion) sidelined for Sunday’s matchup against the Buccaneers. Superstar running back Saquon Barkley will likely carry the load on offense, while wideout Jahan Dotson and tight end Dallas Goedert remain the primary options in the passing game for quarterback Jalen Hurts Sunday.

fields.header: Joe Mixon (ankle) ruled out Sunday
fields.description: Joe Mixon (ankle) has been ruled out for Sunday's game vs the Jaguars. (Source: Adam Schefter on X)
fields.fantasy_impact: Mixon was considered a game-time decision coming into Sunday due to a sprained ankle.  While he is feeling better, the Texans will choose to play it safe with their star running back.  Cam Akers will take the lead in the Texans' backfield on Sunday.

fields.header: Alvin Kamara (hip/ribs) officially active for Week 4
fields.description: Saints RB Alvin Kamara (hip/ribs) is officially active for a Week 4 matchup with the Falcons.
fields.fantasy_impact: Kamara was originally listed as questionable for Week 4, but will suit up in a divisional matchup with Atlanta. Fantasy managers should feel comfortable starting Kamara in Week 4.

fields.header: Chris Olave (hamstring) officially active for Week 4
fields.description: Saints WR Chris Olave (hamstring) is officially active for a Week 4 matchup with the Falcons.
fields.fantasy_impact: Olave was able to test his hamstring injury in pregame warmups and will suit up against the Falcons. Fantasy managers should feel comfortable leave him in their starting lineups.

fields.header: Anthony Richardson (hip) headed to the locker room
fields.description: Colts QB Anthony Richardson is headed to the locker room with an apparent hip injury.  (Source: Brooke Pryor on Twitter )
fields.fantasy_impact: Richardson came off the field limping after a rushing attempt. He returned after missing just one play, but appeared to be in pain after being hit by Minkah Fitzpatrick on a rushing attempt following his return to the game. Joe Flacco is currently in at QB for the Colts and they should provide an update on Richardson’s status soon.

fields.header: Deebo Samuel Sr. (calf) active for Week 4 against Patriots
fields.description: Deebo Samuel Sr. (calf) is officially active for Week 4 for the San Francisco 49ers against the New England Patriots. (Source: San Francisco 49ers on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Samuel Sr. progressed throughout the week for the 49ers and will return to a San Francisco offense in desperate need of the wideout’s dynamic playmaking abilities. Samuel Sr. faces a stiff test against a steady New England defense Sunday.

fields.header: Justin Herbert (ankle) active for Week 4 against Chiefs
fields.description: Justin Herbert (ankle) is officially active and will start at quarterback in Week 4 for the Los Angeles Chargers against the Kansas City Chiefs. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Herbert was able to progress throughout the week after exiting the team’s Week 3 contest with the ankle injury, passing any remaining obstacles during pregame activities Sunday. The dynamic quarterback will look to keep the Los Angeles offense clicking against an elite Kansas City defense while missing both of his starting offensive tackles Sunday.

fields.header: Davante Adams: Raiders 'growing open' to idea of trading WR
fields.description: The Raiders are reportedly "growing open" to the idea of trading Davante Adams. (Source: Vincent Bonsignore on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: According to reports, the Raiders have begun reaching out to teams to gauge interest in Adams. This will remain a situation to monitor. It had been rumored before the season that the Jets could be a possibility if Adams was to be traded to reunite him with Aaron Rodgers.

fields.header: Brandin Cooks to miss Week 5 and potentially longer
fields.description: Cowboys WR Brandin Cooks will have to miss Week 5 and potentially more time, due to an infection that developed in his right knee which followed a necessary procedure that Cooks underwent after remaining in Week 4's game after sustaining an injury. (Source: Todd Archer on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Huge blow for the Dallas offense as they will hope to have their speedy receiver return to play soon. Expect WRs Jalen Tolbert, 	KaVontae Turpin and Jalen Brooks to see increased receiving work in the meantime.

fields.header: Rashee Rice (knee) placed on injured reserve
fields.description: The Chiefs are officially placing Rashee Rice (knee) on injured reserve, leaving him sidelined for at least the next four weeks. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Rice suffered a serious knee injury during Week 4's win over the Chargers, and the team is now officially placing him on injured reserve. The team is waiting for additional testing before determining whether or not the injury is season ending, but either way, he is going to be out for the next four weeks at the very least. This is bad news for Patrick Mahomes and Kansas City's offense as a whole, but it may open up more opportunities for players like Xavier Worthy and Justin Watson moving forward.

fields.header: Romeo Doubs suspended for one game by Green Bay
fields.description: The Packers have suspended WR Romeo Doubs for one game for conduct detrimental to the team.  (Source: Mike Garafolo on Twitter )
fields.fantasy_impact: Doubs did not travel with the team for their Week 5 game and now we have more insight as to why. He reportedly expressed frustration with his current role in the offense during the week, leading to a suspension for conduct detrimental to the team. Dontayvion Wicks and Bo Melton will likely see increased playing time with Doubs suspended.

fields.header: Aaron Jones OUT for rest of game
fields.description: Vikings RB Aaron Jones is ruled out for the rest of Sunday's game vs. the Jets. He suffered a hip injury in the first half.  (Source: Ari Meirov on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Tough blow for the Vikings offense as they will be without one of their top weapons in the second half. Ty Chandler will take over RB1 duties in Jones's absence.

fields.header: Trey McBride (ribs) active for Week 5
fields.description: Trey McBride (ribs) is officially active for Week 5 for the Arizona Cardinals against the San Francisco 49ers. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: McBride carried a questionable designation into the weekend, but was able to progress enough to suit up for the Week 5 divisional contest. The dynamic tight end should see plenty of involvement against a San Francisco defense that will force quarterback Kyler Murray to get rid of the ball quickly.

fields.header: George Kittle (ribs) active for Week 5
fields.description: George Kittle (ribs) is officially active for Week 5 for the San Francisco 49ers against the Arizona Cardinals. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Kittle carried a questionable designation into the weekend, but was able to avoid any setbacks during pregame warmups and will suit up for head coach Kyle Shanahan. The versatile tight end will be a primary option for quarterback Brock Purdy in the passing game against the Cardinals Sunday.

fields.header: Christian Watson (ankle) inactive for Week 5
fields.description: Christian Watson (ankle) is officially inactive for Week 5 for the Green Bay Packers against the Los Angeles Rams. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Watson will not suit up for the Packers, joining Romeo Doubs (suspension) out of the lineup. Dontavion Wicks and Jayden Reed will be the primary options for quarterback Jordan Love in the Green Bay passing attack, with wideout Bo Melton and tight end Tucker Kraft to also receive targets against a middling Rams defense.

fields.header: Devin Singletary (groin) inactive for Week 5
fields.description: Devin Singletary (groin) is officially inactive for Week 5 for the New York Giants against the Seattle Seahawks. (Source: Dan Salomone on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Singletary will miss Sunday’s contest, unable to pass through pregame warmups for the Giants. Tyrone Tracy Jr. and Eric Gray will lead the backfield attack against a steady Seattle defense Sunday.

fields.header: Robert Saleh fired by New York Jets
fields.description: The New York Jets have fired head coach Robert Saleh after a 2-3 start to the season. DC Jeff Ulbrich will be the interim HC. (Source: Adam Schefter on X)
fields.fantasy_impact: Amidst a disappointing start to the season, many wondered if OC Nathaniel Hackett could be fired in an attempt to spark the offense. But Saleh getting fired just five weeks into the season is a stunner. NFL teams with Super Bowl aspirations rarely make such a move this early, since doing so essentially admits they were wrong to keep the HC in the first place. But the Jets are all-in on QB Aaron Rodgers, and it seems likely after last week's awkward exchange between Rodgers and Saleh was caught on camera that there is more to the story here. For now, not much changes for New York's offensive playmakers. This is still Hackett's offense being steered by Rodgers. Unless we hear reports about Saleh impacting the direction on offense, there does not appear to be any immediate fantasy impact for the offensive side of the ball.

fields.header: Nico Collins (hamstring) placed on injured reserve
fields.description: Nico Collins (hamstring) has been placed on injured reserve, knocking him out for the next four weeks at least. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Collins suffered a hamstring injury in Week 5's win over the Bills, and the team is now placing him on injured reserve because of it. He will be out for the next four weeks at the very least, and it's possible that his absence will extend beyond that. This is devastating news for fantasy managers of the young wideout, as he was shaping up to be a league-winner before this injury. Tank Dell, Stefon Diggs, and Dalton Schultz will all benefit from Collins' absence over the next month or so.

fields.header: Malik Nabers (concussion) ruled out Week 6
fields.description: Malik Nabers has been ruled out for Sunday's game against the Bengals. (Source: Jordan Raanan on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Nabers will miss a second straight game as he remains in concussion protocol. Darius Slayton and Wan'Dale Robinson should continue to play a bigger role in the passing game for Daniel Jones.

fields.header: Davante Adams being traded to New York Jets
fields.description: The Raiders are completing a trade of WR Davante Adams to the New York Jets, according to multiple reports. The return for the Raiders is reportedly a conditional third-round pick.  (Source: Ian Rapoport on X)
fields.fantasy_impact: The Jets have been the logical destination for Adams given the Aaron Rodgers connection. Adams has missed the last three games as he deals with a hamstring injury but is expected to be able to return soon. Through three games with the Raiders, the veteran WR caught 18 of his 27 targets for 209 yards and one touchdown. This development isn't great news for WRs Garrett Wilson and Allen Lazard, who will now have a new No. 1 WR to compete with for targets. The offense as a whole should improve, but Adams instantly becomes the top WR in this offense given his talent and his history with Rodgers. As for RB Breece Hall, an improved passing attack could help open things up in the running game.

fields.header: Russell Wilson to get first-team reps, could start Week 7 vs. Jets
fields.description: The Steelers plan to give Russell Wilson first-team reps at practice this week and he could start on Sunday against the Jets. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: It sounds like Wilson could make his first start of the season for Pittsburgh. Justin Fields should still be rostered in 2-QB and superflex leagues, but he can likely be dropped in 1-QB leagues assuming Wilson is officially named the starter.

fields.header: Amari Cooper being traded to Buffalo Bills
fields.description: The Cleveland Browns are trading WR Amari Cooper to the Buffalo Bills, according to multiple reports.  (Source: Jordan Schultz on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Through six games with the Browns, Cooper caught 24 of his 53 targets for 250 yards and two touchdowns. The Cleveland offense has been one of the worst in the NFL, in large part because QB Deshaun Watson continues to struggle. The Bills lost Stefon Diggs and Gabe Davis in the offseason and have been piecing their passing game together with Khalil Shakir, Keon Coleman, Curtis Samuel, and TE Dalton Kincaid. Cooper is the upgrade they needed at WR, and he will step in and immediately be the top target for this passing offense. That means Shakir, who has nearly as many catches as Cooper (20) despite only receiving 21 targets, could see his opportunities decrease. In Cleveland, it means more opportunities for Jerry Jeudy and Elijah Moore, but fantasy managers are probably best avoiding this situation until there is a change at QB.

fields.header: Rashid Shaheed (knee) to miss remainder of season
fields.description: Rashid Shaheed (knee) will miss the remainder of the 2024 season after undergoing a procedure to repair his meniscus. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Shaheed underwent surgery to repair his meniscus on Thursday and is set to miss the remainder of the season while he recovers. He's facing a four-to-six month recovery period, so it's likely that he will be fully ready to go for the 2025 season if all goes to plan with his recovery. This is bad news for New Orleans' offense, as they will now have to look to players like Bub Means, Cedrick Wilson Jr., and Juwan Johnson to step up and play a bigger role in his absence moving forward.

fields.header: Travis Etienne Jr. (hamstring) inactive for Week 7
fields.description: Travis Etienne Jr. (hamstring) is officially inactive for Week 7 for the Jacksonville Jaguars against the New England Patriots. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Etienne Jr. will not suit up for the Jaguars, as the running back looks to use the upcoming bye week to return to full health. Tank Bigsby will receive the majority of the backfield touches while D’Ernest Johnson mixes in for head coach Doug Pederson against the Patriots Sunday.

fields.header: Rhamondre Stevenson (foot) active for Week 7
fields.description: Rhamondre Stevenson (foot) is officially active for Week 7 for the New England Patriots against the Jacksonville Jaguars. (Source: New England Patriots)
fields.fantasy_impact: Stevenson was able to progress enough during pregame activities to suit up for the Patriots, as the running back looks to take advantage of a porous Jacksonville defense Sunday.

fields.header: Kenneth Walker III active vs. Falcons
fields.description: Seahawks RB Kenneth Walker III (illness) will officially be active Sunday vs. the Falcons on his 24th birthday.  (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Walker was added to the injury report and listed as questionable on Saturday because of an illness that came up, but he will still get the start today.

fields.header: Aaron Jones (hamstring) active for Week 7
fields.description: Aaron Jones (hamstring) is officially active for Week 7 for the Minnesota Vikings against the Detroit Lions. (Source: Adam Caplan on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Jones carried a questionable designation into Sunday, but is good to go for the Vikings against a strong Lions run defense in the NFC North divisional clash.

fields.header: Michael Pittman Jr. (back) active for Week 7
fields.description: Michael Pittman Jr. (back) is officially active for the Indianapolis Colts against the Miami Dolphins. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Pittman Jr. was able to clear through pregame warmups for the Colts, giving returning starting quarterback Anthony Richardson his top pass-catching weapon against a tough Miami secondary Sunday.

fields.header: Cooper Kupp (foot) inactive for Week 7
fields.description: Cooper Kupp (foot) is officially inactive for Week 7 for the Los Angeles Rams against the Las Vegas Raiders. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Kupp will remained sidelined for the Rams, as the team hopes another week of rest and practice will benefit the talented pass-catcher. Fantasy managers can expect Tutu Atwell and Demarcus Robinson to lead the Rams wideouts, while running back Kyren Williams looks to take advantage of a generous Las Vegas run defense Sunday.

fields.header: Brandon Aiyuk: 49ers worried about ACL
fields.description: 49ers coach Kyle Shanahan said they are worried that Brandon Aiyuk injured his ACL. (Source: Lindsey Thiry on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Aiyuk will undergo an MRI to confirm the results. His knee appeared to get hit when he was tackled before he had to be carted back to to the locker room during Sunday's game against the Chiefs. There should be more information on his status on Monday.

fields.header: Jameson Williams suspended two games for violating NFL's PES policy
fields.description: Jameson Williams is facing a two-game suspension for violating the NFL’s Performance-Enhancing Substances (PES) policy.  (Source: Eric Woodyard on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Williams will miss the next two games for the Lions. Amon-Ra St. Brown and Sam LaPorta should both see some more targets in his absence.

fields.header: DeAndre Hopkins reportedly being traded to Chiefs
fields.description: The Titans and Chiefs are working on a trade to send veteran WR DeAndre Hopkins to Kansas City, according to a report from ESPN NFL insider Adam Schefter.  (Source: Adam Schefter on X)
fields.fantasy_impact: With the Titans off to a 1-5 start and the Chiefs suffering season-ending injuries to WRs Hollywood Brown and Rashee Rice, this is a connection many analysts made when it first looked like Hopkins could be available. As far as his fantasy value is concerned, this is a best-case scenario for the veteran WR. Kansas City has been piecing things together with rookie WR Xavier Worthy, Justin Watson, JuJu Smith-Schuster, Mecole Hardman, and Skyy Moore. Assuming he can pick up the offense quickly, Hopkins should step in and immediately be one of the top options in the passing game for QB Patrick Mahomes.  Hopkins was WR54 in the FantasyPros ROS Rankings before this trade, but this move should bump him all the way up into WR3 territory. In Tennessee, this should mean more opportunities for Calvin Ridley and Tyler Boyd, but fantasy managers would be wise not to trust that Titans offense if they can avoid it.

fields.header: Bryce Young expected to start Week 8
fields.description: Bryce Young is expected to be Carolina's starting quarterback in Week 8. (Source: Darin Gantt on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: The Panthers are planning on starting Young in Week 8 due to the thumb injury that Andy Dalton is dealing with. The 23-year old was benched earlier in the season after a couple of rough games, but he will have a chance now to earn more opportunities for himself in the future. This isn't good news for players like Diontae Johnson (ribs) and Chuba Hubbard, who have seen a massive increase in fantasy value ever since Young has been benched.

fields.header: Tee Higgins (quad) officially inactive for Week 8
fields.description: Cincinnati Bengals WR Tee Higgins is officially inactive against the Philadelphia Eagles in Week 8 as he deals with a late quad injury (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: The Bengals listed Higgins late with a quad injury, and he will not be available for Week 8 after not being seen during warmups. Higgins has a history of soft-tissue injuries, and fans certainly hope this will not develop into a multi-week injury as is common for Higgins. WR Andrei Iosivas and TE Mike Gesicki will likely see increased snaps and targets like they did when Higgins was out early in the year with a hamstring injury, and rookie WR Jermaine Burton is a deep player to monitor.

fields.header: Deebo Samuel Sr. (wrist/illness) active for Week 8
fields.description: Deebo Samuel Sr. (wrist/illness) is officially active for Week 8 for the San Francisco 49ers against the Dallas Cowboys. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Samuel Sr. is good to go after carrying a questionable designation into the weekend, giving a boost to a shorthanded San Francisco offense against a struggling Dallas Cowboys defense Sunday night. The dynamic wideout should see as many touches as he can handle for head coach Kyle Shanahan.

fields.header: George Kittle (foot) active for Week 8
fields.description: George Kittle (foot) is officially active for Week 8 for the San Francisco 49ers against the Dallas Cowboys. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Kittle will suit up after entering the weekend with a questionable designation for the 49ers, giving quarterback Brock Purdy a game-breaking option in the passing game against a struggling Dallas defense for head coach Kyle Shanahan Sunday night.

fields.header: Christian Kirk suffers broken collarbone in loss to Packers
fields.description: Christian Kirk suffered a broken collarbone in the Jaguars’ 30-27 loss to the Packers on Sunday. Before exiting, he caught two of five targets for 59 yards.
fields.fantasy_impact: While it may not be the biggest blow to the Jaguars, with rumors circulating that they were going to trade the receiver and might have planned to be without his services soon anyway, it is a big blow for Kirk himself. He should recover from the injury well before the start of next season, but his trade value has plummeted. He is still under contract for the Jags next season, but there are potential outs the team could take, making him a free agent. Coming off of an injury as a free agent is not ideal, but that is mere speculation. For now, Kirk remains a Jaguar and will look to rebuild his value next year.

fields.header: Stefon Diggs confirmed to be out for season with knee injury
fields.description: Stefon Diggs is officially out for the season due to a knee injury. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: This was the expectation after Diggs left Sunday's game with a non-contact knee injury. It is a tough break for Diggs who is set to enter free agency this offseason. With Nico Collins also still sidelined, Tank Dell should take over the clear No. 1 wide receiver role for now with Dalton Schultz likely also taking on a bigger role.

fields.header: Anthony Richardson benched for Joe Flacco
fields.description: The Colts are benching Anthony Richardson for Joe Flacco. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: The move was made by the coaches Tuesday morning. Flacco should bring more stability to Michael Pittman, Josh Downs and the entire Colts offense. Flacco will be in the QB2 range for fantasy managers in 2-QB and superflex leagues.

fields.header: Diontae Johnson reportedly traded to Baltimore
fields.description: Diontae Johnson is heading to the Baltimore Ravens according to ESPN's sources. (Source: Adam Schefter on X)
fields.fantasy_impact: Johnson being dealt to Baltimore is big fantasy news, with notable implications for the Ravens' pass catchers. This trade will likely boost Johnson's fantasy stock, even if he sees fewer targets overall. Baltimore’s offense is much more efficient than Carolina’s, ranking 2nd in yards per pass, 3rd in passing touchdowns, and 5th in passing yards per game. Johnson likely steps in as the WR2, with Zay Flowers remaining the WR1. This addition could siphon targets from tight ends Isaiah Likely and Mark Andrews. Rashod Bateman's role will be interesting to watch, but given how often Flowers lines up in the slot, Bateman may be insulated from a drop-off in usage. It is worth noting that Bateman was a 1st round draft pick for the Ravens in 2021, and he has played well this season. Nelson Agholor may be the odd man out, although he can also play in the slot if Flowers shifts outside.

fields.header: DK Metcalf (knee) ruled out for Sunday
fields.description: The Seahawks have officially ruled out WR DK Metcalf for Sunday's game against Rams. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter )
fields.fantasy_impact: Metcalf is dealing with an MCL sprain and has yet to practice this week. Fantasy managers should expect Jaxon Smith-Njigba, Tyler Lockett, and Jake Bobo to see increased snaps against the Rams.

fields.header: Brian Robinson Jr. (hamstring) inactive against Giants
fields.description: Brian Robinson Jr. (hamstring) is officially inactive for Week 9 for the Washington Commanders against the New York Giants. (Source: Mike Garofolo on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Robinson Jr. was unable to clear through pregame activities and will not suit up for head coach Dan Quinn. Austin Ekeler will lead the Washington backfield with Jeremy McNichols mixing in against the Giants as well.

fields.header: Josh Jacobs (ankle) active for Week 9
fields.description: Josh Jacobs (ankle) is officially active for Week 9 for the Green Bay Packers against the Detroit Lions. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Jacobs was able to progress through pregame activities without any setbacks despite not practicing to end the week, joining quarterback Jordan Love (groin) in the starting lineup to boost the Green Bay offense against the Lions Sunday.

fields.header: Jordan Love (groin) active for Week 9
fields.description: Jordan Love (groin) is officially active for Week 9 for the Green Bay Packers against the Detroit Lions. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter )
fields.fantasy_impact: Love will return to start behind center after exiting Week 8 due to suffering the groin injury. The talented signal-caller will look to stay upright in hopes of taking advantage of an overly aggressive Detroit secondary Sunday.

fields.header: Puka Nacua (knee) active for Week 9
fields.description: Puka Nacua (knee) is officially active for Week 9 for the Los Angeles Rams against the Seattle Seahawks. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Nacua will suit up after passing through pregame warmups without any setbacks, giving quarterback Matthew Stafford his two primary pass-catching options along with fellow wideout Cooper Kupp against the Seahawks Sunday.

fields.header: CeeDee Lamb (shoulder) questionable to return in Week 9
fields.description: CeeDee Lamb (shoulder) is questionable to return in Week 9 for the Dallas Cowboys against the Atlanta Falcons according to Jane Slater. (Source: Jane Slater on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Lamb suffered the apparent injury late in the fourth quarter and the Cowboys trailing 27-13. The wideout hauled in eight of 12 targets for 47 yards while also rushing twice for 15 yards prior to the injury.

fields.header: Trevor Lawrence (shoulder) likely to miss Week 10
fields.description: Jacksonville Jaguars QB Trevor Lawrence is unlikely to play in Week 10 as he is working through his shoulder injury. He is considered day-to-day and is evaluating multiple options, including potentially surgery. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: With Lawrence out, Mac Jones is in at QB, his first start in a Jaguars uniform and for his hometown team. After a rough start to the year, Lawrence has begun to turn it around in recent weeks. However, his situation should be monitored if he is forced to miss extended time.

fields.header: Amari Cooper (wrist) ruled out again for Week 10
fields.description: Buffalo Bills WR Amari Cooper is being ruled out for Week 10 against the Indianapolis Colts with his ongoing wrist injury. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Cooper is missing his second game in a row, now being absent for two of three since being traded to Buffalo. He's been dealing with a wrist injury, and despite being listed as questionable, he will not suit up. He said earlier this week he was still getting used to catching the ball again and was sporting a soft cast, so his situation should be monitored leading into Week 11.

fields.header: Tyreek Hill (wrist) active vs. Rams
fields.description: Tyreek Hill is officially active for Monday night's game against Los Angeles. (Source: Adam Schefter on X.com)
fields.fantasy_impact: Hill is set to lace them up on Monday night despite not practicing Friday or Saturday. The 30-year-old is having a down year by his standards, thanks in part to quarterback injuries. However, his 446 receiving yards still lead the Dolphins and he is averaging 13.1 yards per reception. Fantasy managers should feel confident firing up Hill in their lineups, despite the wrist, as the return of Tua Tagovailoa has returned his weekly fantasy potential to elite status.

fields.header: Dak Prescott to undergo season-ending hamstring surgery
fields.description: Cowboys QB Dak Prescott will undergo season-ending surgery on his injured hamstring Wednesday.  (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter )
fields.fantasy_impact: Prescott is dealing with a partial avulsion of his hamstring, according to Jerry Jones. Prescott will be placed on injured reserve and he will turn his focus to rehabbing for the 2025 season. The Cowboys are expected to continue to start Cooper Rush at QB, which will be a downgrade for the Cowboys’ pass catchers for the remainder of the season.

fields.header: Christian McCaffrey (knee) placed on injured reserve
fields.description: Christian McCaffrey (knee) has been placed on injured reserve by the San Francisco 49ers. (Source: Clayton Holloway on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: McCaffrey will miss at least the next six weeks according to head coach Kyle Shanahan, ending the running back’s regular season. With backup Jordan Mason (ankle) also headed to injured reserve, Isaac Guerendo will now likely be thrust into a starting role, making the third-string running back worthy of a waiver pickup ahead of Week 14.

fields.header: Trevor Lawrence (concussion) placed on injured reserve
fields.description: Trevor Lawrence (concussion) has been placed on injured reserve by the Jacksonville Jaguars according to Ian Rapoport. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Lawrence will miss at least the next four games, with the possibility of being shut down for the season, as the quarterback is also still dealing with a right shoulder injury and Jacksonville is not in postseason contention whatsoever. Backup Mac Jones will remain the starting quarterback with Lawrence sidelined, with a Week 14 contest against the Tennessee Titans ahead.

fields.header: Josh Jacobs (calf) off injury report for Week 14
fields.description: Josh Jacobs (calf) is off the injury report and will play in Week 14 for the Green Bay Packers against the Detroit Lions according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Jacobs was limited in practice to begin the week with the calf injury, but will receive another full workload against an injury-ravaged Detroit front seven in the pivotal divisional clash Thursday night.

fields.header: George Pickens (hamstring) inactive for Week 14
fields.description: George Pickens (hamstring) is officially inactive for Week 14 for the Pittsburgh Steelers against the Cleveland Browns according to Dianna Russini. (Source: Dianna Russini on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Pickens was unable to clear through pregame warmups and will now sit out against the Browns Sunday. Fantasy managers can expect Calvin Austin and Mike Williams to see increased targets in Week 14.

fields.header: Jakobi Meyers (ankle) active for Week 14
fields.description: Jakobi Meyers (ankle) is officially active for Week 14 for the Las Vegas Raiders against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Meyers passed through pregame warmups without any setbacks after entering the weekend carrying a questionable designation, slotting the wideout into potential WR1 territory in PPR formats as one of quarterback Aidan O’Connell’s primary targets against an underwhelming Tampa Bay defense in Week 14.

fields.header: Alexander Mattison (ankle) inactive for Week 14
fields.description: Alexander Mattison (ankle) is officially inactive for Week 14 for the Las Vegas Raiders against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Mattison will join Zamir White (quad) out of the lineup for the Raiders, leaving head coach Antonio Pierce with Sincere McCormick and Ameer Abdullah to handle the backfield work against the Buccaneers Sunday.

fields.header: Malik Nabers (hip/groin) active for Week 14
fields.description: Malik Nabers (hip/groin) is officially active for Week 14 for the New York Giants against the New Orleans Saints according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Nabers passed through pregame warmups without any setbacks, clearing the rookie pass-catcher to suit up for head coach Brian Daboll. The wideout may see a decreased workload according to Schefter, but fantasy managers will likely still insert the wideout in lineups hoping for WR1 potential against a New Orleans secondary Sunday.

fields.header: Keon Coleman (wrist) inactive for Week 14
fields.description: Keon Coleman (wrist) is officially inactive for Week 14 for the Buffalo Bills against the Los Angeles Rams. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Coleman was unable to pass through pregame warmups without any setbacks for the Bills, relegating the pass-catcher to the sidelines for Sunday’s contest. Khalil Shakir and Amari Cooper will likely absorb any additional targets against the Rams for head coach Sean McDermott.

fields.header: D’Andre Swift (quad) active for Week 14
fields.description: D’Andre Swift (quad) is officially active for Week 14 for the Chicago Bears against the San Francisco 49ers according to Patrick Finley. (Source: Patrick Finley on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Swift is good to go after entering the weekend carrying a questionable designation, giving quarterback Caleb Williams his No. 1 running back against a tough San Francisco defense Sunday.

fields.header: DJ Moore (quad) active for Week 14
fields.description: DJ Moore (quad) is officially active for Week 14 for the Chicago Bears against the San Francisco 49ers according to Patrick Finley. (Source: Patrick Finley on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Moore passed through pregame warmups without any setbacks after entering the weekend carrying a questionable designation for the Bears. The wideout should once again be one of rookie quarterback Caleb Williams’s primary option in the Chicago offense against the San Francisco 49ers Sunday.

fields.header: Derek Carr fractures non-throwing hand
fields.description: Derek Carr has suffered a fracture in his non-throwing hand and is expected to miss several weeks. (Source: Ian Rapoport)
fields.fantasy_impact: While the Saints may not immediately place Carr on injured reserve, he is expected to be sidelined for a significant period. This is a major blow to the Saints offense and fantasy managers alike. Carr's absence leaves a void under center, and the team's offensive production is likely to suffer. Fantasy managers should adjust their lineups accordingly and look for alternative quarterback options.

fields.header: Jonathon Brooks re-tore his ACL
fields.description: Jonathon Brooks has re-torn his right ACL, according to head coach Dave Canales. (Source: Tom Pelissero)
fields.fantasy_impact: This is a devastating blow for Brooks, the first running back selected in the NFL Draft in April. After a long wait, he finally made his NFL debut on November 24th and appeared in three games before this unfortunate injury. Brooks now faces another lengthy rehabilitation process. Expect Chuba Hubbard to continue leading the Panthers backfield.

fields.header: Tony Pollard (ankle) active for Week 15
fields.description: Tony Pollard (ankle) is officially active for Week 15 for the Tennessee Titans against the Cincinnati Bengals according to Ian Rapoport. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Pollard was able to pass through pregame warmups without any setbacks, setting the running back up for a sizeable workload against a struggling Cincinnati run defense Sunday. Fantasy managers can expect RB2 production with upside.

fields.header: David Njoku (hamstring) inactive for Week 15
fields.description: David Njoku (hamstring) is officially inactive for Week 15 for the Cleveland Browns against the Kansas City Chiefs according to Ian Rapoport. (Source: Ian Rapoport on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Njoku was unable to clear through pregame activities for the Browns, leaving the offense shorthanded against a strong Kansas City defense. With Cedric Tillman also sidelined, wideouts Jerry Jeudy and Elijah Moore will likely see as many targets as they can handle from quarterback Jameis Winston.

fields.header: Bucky Irving (back/hip) active for Week 15
fields.description: Bucky Irving (back/hip) is officially active for Week 15 for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers against the Los Angeles Chargers according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Irving was able to clear through pregame warmups without any setbacks, returning to a lead role in a productive Tampa Bay backfield attack against a tough Chargers defense for head coach Todd Bowles Sunday.

fields.header: Ladd McConkey (knee/shoulder) active for Week 15
fields.description: Ladd McConkey (knee/shoulder) is officially active for Week 15 for the Los Angeles Chargers against the Tampa Bay Buccaneers according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: McConkey will suit up after carrying a questionable designation into the weekend, clearing through pregame warmups without any setbacks. The rookie wideout will likely receive as many targets as he can handle as the primary option in the Los Angeles passing offense for head coach Jim Harbaugh against the Buccaneers.

fields.header: Dalton Kincaid (knee) active for Week 15
fields.description: Dalton Kincaid (knee) is officially active for Week 15 for the Buffalo Bills against the Detroit Lions according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Kincaid will take the field for the first time since Week 10 for the Bills, providing quarterback Josh Allen with a reliable intermediate passing option against a tough Detroit Lions defense Sunday.

fields.header: Kenneth Walker III (calf) inactive for Week 15
fields.description: Kenneth Walker III (calf) is officially inactive for Week 15 for the Seattle Seahawks against the Green Bay Packers. (Source: Seattle Seahawks on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Walker III will sit out the Week 15 contest after being unable to clear through pregame warmups for the Seahawks. Zach Charbonnet will handle the majority of the backfield work against a solid Green Bay defense Sunday night.

fields.header: David Montgomery (knee) to undergo season-ending surgery
fields.description: Detroit Lions RB David Montgomery will undergo season-ending knee surgery after suffering an MCL injury in Week 15's loss to the Buffalo Bills. (Source: Colton Pouncy on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Montgomery had been a standout all season as a part of the potent Detroit offense, playing alongside RB Jahmyr Gibbs. The former Chicago Bears RB had 12 TDs on the ground and 775 rushing yards after rushing for 1,015 yards and 13 TDs the year before. Gibbs will likely slide into a more full-time role in the Lions' offense, but if they try to incorporate another RB, it could be a mixture of Craig Reynolds, Jermar Jefferson and/or rookie Sione Vaki.

fields.header: Michael Penix Jr. named Falcons starter for Week 16
fields.description: The Falcons have named Michael Penix Jr. the starter at quarterback heading into Week 16 against the Giants. (Source: Mike Garafolo on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: It seemed to be only a matter of time until Kirk Cousins would be benched following his struggles over the past month. The first-round pick out of Washington will get his first chance to start on Sunday. Penix will offer the Falcons offense more upside all-around for Bijan Robinson, Drake London, Darnell Mooney and Kyle Pitts for fantasy managers.

fields.header: Rashod Bateman (foot) active for Week 16
fields.description: Rashod Bateman (foot) is officially active for Week 16 for the Baltimore Ravens against the Pittsburgh Steelers according to Jamison Hensley. (Source: Jamison Hensley on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Bateman is good to go after testing his injured foot during pregame warmups for the Ravens, giving quarterback Lamar Jackson all of his primary options in the Baltimore passing attack against a tough Pittsburgh defense Saturday.

fields.header: Alvin Kamara (groin) ruled out for Week 16
fields.description: Alvin Kamara (groin) has been ruled out for Week 16 for the New Orleans Saints against the Green Bay Packers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Kamara will sit out after suffering the groin injury in Week 15, leading to Kendre Miller receiving the majority of backfield touches with Jamaal Williams getting mixed in against the Packers Monday night.

fields.header: Chris Olave (head) ruled out for Week 16
fields.description: Chris Olave (head) has been ruled out for Week 16 for the New Orleans Saints against the Green Bay Packers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Olave will remain out for the Saints despite having his practice window opened and logging a limited practice season Thursday, leaving the New Orleans offense shorthanded against a stout Green Bay defense Monday night.

fields.header: Tony Pollard (ankle) active for Week 16
fields.description: Tony Pollard (ankle) is officially active for the Tennessee Titans against the Indianapolis Colts according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Pollard was able to pass through pregame warmups without any setbacks for head coach Brian Callahan, giving the Tennessee offense its most reliable option against an inconsistent Indianapolis defense in the AFC South showdown. Pollard offers fantasy managers a steady RB2 option with upside this week.

fields.header: David Njoku (hamstring) active for Week 16
fields.description: David Njoku (hamstring) is officially active for Week 16 for the Cleveland Browns against the Cincinnati Bengals according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Njoku cleared through pregame warmups without any issues and is good to go against the Bengals. The tight end could be a primary option in a Cleveland passing offense starting a third different quarterback this season against Cincinnati Sunday.

fields.header: Tyrone Tracy Jr. (ankle) active for Week 16
fields.description: Tyrone Tracy Jr. (ankle) is officially active for Week 16 for the New York Giants against the Atlanta Falcons according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Tracy Jr. tested the injured ankle during pregame warmups without any setbacks, and should retake his starting role in the backfield for head coach Brian Daboll against an inconsistent Atlanta Falcons defense Sunday.

fields.header: Zach Ertz (concussion) active for Week 16
fields.description: Zach Ertz (concussion) is officially active for Week 16 for the Washington Commanders against the Philadelphia Eagles according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Ertz will suit up for the Commanders after clearing through league protocols this week, giving rookie quarterback Jayden Daniels one of his favorite targets back against a tough Philadelphia defense Sunday.

fields.header: Jalen Hurts (concussion) ruled out for remainder of Week 16
fields.description: Jalen Hurts (concussion) has been ruled out for the remainder of the Week 16 contest between the Philadelphia Eagles and Washington Commanders according to Tom Pelissero. (Source: Tom Pelissero on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Hurts suffered the concussion in the first quarter, rushing three times for 41 yards and completing 1-of-4 pass attempts for 11 yards before exiting. Kenny Pickett will operate behind center for the remainder of the Week 16 contest against the Commanders.

fields.header: Tyreek Hill (wrist/personal) active for Week 16
fields.description: Tyreek Hill (wrist/personal) is officially active for Week 16 for the Miami Dolphins against the San Francisco 49ers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Hill will suit up after passing through pregame warmups without any setbacks and could be in line for an even larger role in the Miami passing attack with Jaylen Waddle out against the San Francisco 49ers Sunday.

fields.header: Jaylen Waddle (knee) inactive for Week 16
fields.description: Jaylen Waddle (knee) is officially inactive for Week 16 for the  Miami Dolphins against the San Francisco 49ers according to Adam Schefter. (Source: Adam Schefter on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Waddle will sit out the Week 16 contest after entering the weekend carrying a doubtful designation, leaving the Miami offense without a key option against the 49ers. Jonnu Smith, Tyreek Hill, and De’Von Achane should receive all of the volume they can handle from quarterback Tua Tagovailoa Sunday.

fields.header: Cade Otton (knee) inactive for Week 16
fields.description: Cade Otton (knee) is officially inactive for Week 16 for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers against the Dallas Cowboys. (Source: Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Twitter)
fields.fantasy_impact: Otton will not suit up for the Sunday night contest after being unable to practice with the knee injury throughout the week. Wideouts Mike Evans and Jalen McMillan will look to take advantage of an injury-ravaged Dallas secondary for head coach Todd Bowles Sunday night.
